using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace MarvelHeroes.DpsMeter.Services;

/// <summary>
/// Maps a power prototype's enum index to a human-readable display name --
/// e.g. <c>55311u -&gt; "Team Buff Empowered 5 Seconds"</c>.  Surfaced in the buff-tracker
/// diagnostic log and (eventually) the active-buffs UI strip so users see "Empowered" instead
/// of "0xD80F".
///
/// <para>Generated by <c>scripts/GeneratePrototypeNames.ps1</c> from the power dump file emitted
/// by <c>scripts/PrototypeEnumDumper</c>.  Re-run after pulling a fresh dump from a different
/// Calligraphy.sip version.  Names are auto-derived from the path basename with CamelCase
/// split for readability; for tricky cases edit this file directly or refine the cleanup
/// heuristics in the generator.</para>
///
/// <para>The dictionary is large (thousands of entries) but compiles fast and adds negligible
/// startup cost -- the dictionary literal is hoisted into a static field and the hash buckets
/// build once on first access.</para>
/// </summary>
internal static class PowerNames
{
    /// <summary>Returns the display name for <paramref name="prototypeEnumIndex"/>, or
    /// <c>null</c> when the index is unmapped (older Calligraphy version, custom server, or
    /// a non-existent prototype id).  Callers should fall back to printing the raw hex id in
    /// that case so logs stay searchable.</summary>
    public static string? Get(uint prototypeEnumIndex)
        => s_names.TryGetValue(prototypeEnumIndex, out var n) ? n : null;

